The automatic authentication check is due to useEffect

so inside UserContext.jsx useEffect runs and fetches user data. even no user requests it manually or through some clicking , the url /api/user/currentuser route hits through useEffect in UserContext.jsx inside getcurrUser function. then in backend usercontroller route hits with the same url /api/user/currentuser [like we handle signup with Signuphandler function which connects frontend functioning with backend routing using axios] then backend sends user data from backend in console in browser. after that in frontend inside the same getcurrUser function user information sets using setUserData.....the whole thing is about useEffect



...Making Sidebar,
while displaying Username and Headline in the sidebar, i needed UserDataContext again which runs every time page refreshes, so the Userdata dont get lost after page reload. my App is wrapped with the UserDataContext which provide three things
1-loading, a false boolean value till page loads(or userData gets set[/api/user/currentuser]).  
2-userData, actual data of the user loggedin(User with Session)
3-SetUserData, this function allows to reset the userData on any page like EditProfile.jsx or something.
So we are using two normal variables {userData, loading} (not useState variables) and store whatever the UserDataContext provides throung these states like  
<UserDataContext.Provider value={{ userData, setUserData, loading }}>
    {children}
</UserDataContext.Provider>
finally use it for displaying username and headline in the Sidebar.